{
  "text": ". The function f is submodular and non-decreasing. P . To prove the submodularity we show that viol(·) is supermodular with respect to strong edges. This makes tri(·) submodular with respect to strong edges, which in turn makes f submodular with respect to weak edges. For the last implication it is wellknown that a function is submodular if and only if its complement is submodular. [CITATION_1] Let S be a set of strong edges. This proves that viol(·) is a supermodular set function of edges.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8478459"
